{
  "stem": "12462.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I wanted one of two jobs at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One was as an attorney of the National Labor Relations Board, because I was very interested in strengthening the unions in the country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the other was antitrust division of the Department of Justice.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the reason was because I felt there was too much big business and monopoly in the country.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1938.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the fall of '38, I took this brief I had mentioned, and I went down, and I went into the office of the general counsel, Charles Fay of the National Labor Relations Board.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he and his associate, a man by the name of Watts, hired me within one half hour.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I never got to the Department of Justice to make an application there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In September of 1938.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I stayed with them until [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] early May 1942, but I was moved around the country a lot because I very quickly was put into the trial section.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was given, after a little breaking in, and often without enough breaking in, the assignment to try a number of cases in San Diego and Chicago and the backwoods of West Virginia and so on.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Unfair labor practices underneath the National Labor Relations Act, which had been passed in 1935, and which had been found constitutional by the Supreme Court after a long fight.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] well, that's pretty much it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I found it very interesting.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can remember my first trial, which was in San Diego with the Star and Crescent Boat Company, which had been engaged in firing union employees and in trying to form a little company union.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
